title: USB-C Headphones no audio but volume rocker works
content:
I have been using the Google USB-C Earbuds for a while now, but recently they, and my other USB-C earbuds have stopped working. I cleaned out my USB-C port, but it didn't solve the issue. The earbuds show up in the connection settings with "Charging connected device".

The weirdest thing is that the volume and media buttons all function normally. I have tried booting into safe mode, but it had the same effect. I am running Android Q beta 3 on my Pixel 2.
